Description: The return of the Holy Family from Egypt; the Virgin holding the Christ Child seated next to St Joseph at centre at the bottom of steps leading up to an inn at right; another traveller carrying a basket and walking up the stairs behind them. Etching and engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Moyses van Wtenbrouck
Curator's comments: This is fourth state, for comment and an impression of first state see S.2940.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (18.IV)
Subjects: return of the holy family from egypt
Acquisition notes: For the history of the acquisition of the Sheepshanks collection, please see Sheepshanks.1
